caption:
An American alligator was spotted in the Everglades with its upper jaw missing, exposing tissue and part of its snout. 

Despite the severe injury, it appeared active and free-ranging, with no signs of captivity. It’s unclear how the animal is surviving, raising the question of whether such cases have been observed in the wild before.
